The draws for the fourth and fifth rounds of the FA Cup will be made on Monday evening. Liverpool secured progress from round three with Friday’s 4-1 win at Aston Villa. And the Reds will discover their opponents in the competition’s next stage, as well as their potential opposition in round five, from 7.10pm GMT on Monday. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! Both draws, which are taking place back-to-back to aid with fixture scheduling, will be broadcast live on BT Sport 1 in the UK. Fourth-round ties are scheduled to take place over the weekend of January 23-24, with fifth-round matches then set for midweek in the week commencing Monday February 8.